      <section eId="sec_11_0308">
        <num>11-0308</num>
        <heading>Sale of small lead fishing sinkers prohibited</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_11_0308__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>"sinker" shall mean any device that is designed to be attached to\na fishing line and intended to sink the line. Such term shall not\ninclude artificial lures, weighted line, weighted flies or jig heads.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_11_0308__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>"sell at retail" or "retail sale" shall mean the sale to any\nperson in the state for any purpose other than for resale.\n  3. The department shall provide notice of the prohibition of the\nretail sale or offering for sale of lead fishing sinkers weighing\none-half ounce or less in the state fishing regulations guide.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
